# Overriding and Super in Java

This project demonstrates the concepts of **Method Overriding** and the **super keyword** in Java.

## 📖 Overview

Method Overriding is a feature in Java where a subclass provides a specific implementation of a method that is already defined in its parent class.

The `super` keyword is used to:

- Access parent class methods
- Access parent class variables
- Invoke parent class constructors

## 🚀 Features

- Demonstrates inheritance in Java
- Shows method overriding
- Uses `super` to call parent class methods
- Uses `super` to access parent class variables

## 💻 Example

```java
class Parent {
    void display() {
        System.out.println("Parent class method");
    }
}

class Child extends Parent {
    @Override
    void display() {
        super.display();
        System.out.println("Child class method");
    }
}
Output
Parent class method
Child class method

